    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330.1/7–3050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-30T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 30, 1950—9 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>542. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>s 518 and 528, July 28.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d175fn1">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_307">p.
                        307</ref>.</note> I saw Parodi<note n="2" xml:id="d175fn2">Alexandre Parodi,
                        Secretary-General of the French Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</note> this
                    subject yesterday and again today making strong plea for favorable attitude.
                        Schuman<note n="3" xml:id="d175fn3">Robert Schuman, French Minister of
                        Foreign Affairs.</note> is absent until Wednesday night but Parodi had
                    discussed it with him. French attitude unfortunately characterized by great
                    reserve as communicated noon today to Chauvel of which you no doubt already
                    informed.</p>
                <p>Department pass New York. Sent Department 542, repeated info <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> New York 3, London 160.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
